xt"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [1,5,4,5]\nOutput: 16\nExplanation: Choosing the indices i=1 and j=3 (indexed from 0), you will get the maximum value of (5-1)*(5-1) = 16.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: nums = [3,7]\nOutput: 12","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= nums.length <= 500`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10^3`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Sorting","Heap (Priority Queue)"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Given the array of integers `nums`, you will choose two different indices `i` and `j` of that array. *Return the maximum value of* `(nums[i]-1)*(nums[j]-1)`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [3,4,5,2]\nOutput: 12 \nExplanation: If you choose the indices i=1 and j=2 (indexed from 0), you will get the maximum value, that is, (nums[1]-1)*(nums[2]-1) = (4-1)*(5-1) = 3*4 = 12.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [1,5,4,5]\nOutput: 16\nExplanation: Choosing the indices i=1 and j=3 (indexed from 0), you will get the maximum value of (5-1)*(5-1) = 16.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: nums = [3,7]\nOutput: 12\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= nums.length <= 500`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10^3`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-product-of-two-elements-in-an-array/","problemName":"Maximum Product of Two Elements in an Array","problemNumber":1464,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given the array of integers `nums`, you will choose two different indices `i` and `j` of that array. *Return the maximum value of* `(nums[i]-1)*(nums[j]-1)`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [3,4,5,2]\nOutput: 12 \nExplanation: If you choose the indices i=1 and j=2 (indexed from 0), you will get the maximum value, that is, (nums[1]-1)*(nums[2]-1) = (4-1)*(5-1) = 3*4 = 12. ","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [1,5,4,5]\nOutput: 16\nExplanation: Choosing the indices i=1 and j=3 (indexed from 0), you will get the maximum value of (5-1)*(5-1) = 16.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: nums = [3,7]\nOutput: 12","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= nums.length <= 500`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10^3`","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Easy","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"Given the array of integers `nums`, you will choose two different indices `i` and `j` of that array. *Return the maximum value of* `(nums[i]-1)*(nums[j]-1)`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [3,4,5,2]\nOutput: 12 \nExplanation: If you choose the indices i=1 and j=2 (indexed from 0), you will get the maximum value, that is, (nums[1]-1)*(nums[2]-1) = (4-1)*(5-1) = 3*4 = 12.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [1,5,4,5]\nOutput: 16\nExplanation: Choosing the indices i=1 and j=3 (indexed from 0), you will get the maximum value of (5-1)*(5-1) = 16.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: nums = [3,7]\nOutput: 12\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= nums.length <= 500`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10^3`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-product-of-two-elements-in-an-array/","problemName":"Maximum Product of Two Elements in an Array","problemNumber":1464,"problemSlug":"maximum-product-of-two-elements-in-an-array","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1464,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[{"assetIndex":0,"bytes":3033,"contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1465-maximum-area-of-a-piece-of-cake-after-horizontal-and-vertical-cuts/1465-leetcode_max_area_2.png","originalUrl":"../../../images/1465-leetcode_max_area_2.png","sha256":"f0d8de10735ea1b9aed6babb54c4d1f904c7a32fa596f87e77b048afe4dc1fb0"},{"assetIndex":1,"bytes":2773,"contentType":